author: Staff Reports
title: PREP CROSS COUNTRY: Cullman boys place 2nd at Athens Bible Invitational; Lady Bearcats finish 5th overall
text:
Larger font size Posted: Friday, October 23, 2015 5:07 pm 
Cullman’s cross country squads turned in a pair of fine performances during Thursday’s Athens Bible Invitational. 
The Bearcats boys finished second overall in the large-school division, while the girls claimed fifth. 
Joey Franklin (seventh, 17:03), Tucker Franey (eighth, 17:04), Tucker Adkison (10th, 17:11), Eli Wilhite (13th, 17:26) and Jackson Tucker (16th, 17:46) helped Cullman place just 13 points shy of Class 7A Grissom in the stacked field of 17 programs. 
Rachael Collins ran a 21:33 for the Lady Bearcats en route to their finish, while Lexy Sivley (18th, 22:18), Kendall Adkison (19th, 22:23), Alexandria Holt (34th, 23:28) and Mattie Green (45th, 24:29) contributed to the squad score in the 15-school event.
